# Prefix `not` is right-associative unary (spec/grammar.md:187, `unary ::= "not" unary | ...`),
# so `not not :a` nests two Call nodes, and a parenthesized single operand `(not :a)` is read as
# a plain grouped expression (no ParenCall) because `not` is not one of the paren-variadic heads.
:a = true
print not :a
print not not :a
print (not :a)
